WEBVTT

00:04.238 --> 00:05.205 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Good evening.

00:05.239 --> 00:06.206 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
I'm Judy Woodruff.

00:06.240 --> 00:08.008 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
On the "NewsHour" tonight:

00:08.041 --> 00:10.444 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
SAMANTHA POWER, U.S. Ambassador
to the United
Nations: I think about Syria
when I go to

00:10.477 --> 00:12.279 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
bed at night.

00:12.312 --> 00:16.683 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: I sit down with
outgoing U.N.
Ambassador Samantha Power to
talk the crisis

00:16.717 --> 00:20.053 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
in Syria, the threat of Russia,
and more.

00:20.087 --> 00:26.393 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Then: how cities are helping
chronically sick
patients cut back on expensive
emergency room

00:26.426 --> 00:29.496 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
visits by getting to the root of
America's
health issues.

00:29.529 --> 00:31.331 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
DR.

00:31.365 --> 00:33.166 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
JEFFREY BRENNER, Camden
Coalition of Healthcare
Providers: I think we're in a
20-year arc

00:33.200 --> 00:36.436 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
of recalibrating and rethinking
what is health
and what is health care, what is
the purpose

00:36.470 --> 00:39.239 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
of our health care system, what
are we trying
to accomplish?

00:39.273 --> 00:44.978 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: And The Obama
Years series
continues with a look at race in
America under

00:45.012 --> 00:46.980 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
the nation's first black
president.

00:47.014 --> 00:54.788 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
All that and more on tonight's
"PBS NewsHour."

00:54.821 --> 00:57.724 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
(BREAK)

00:57.758 --> 01:07.601 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: President-elect
Donald Trump
faces a growing Democratic
boycott this evening,

01:07.634 --> 01:11.338 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
with his inauguration ceremony
just three
days away.

01:11.371 --> 01:16.710 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Congressman John Lewis and
nearly 50 House
Democrats say they will not
attend.

01:16.743 --> 01:21.315 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Lewis had said it would be the
first inauguration
he's missed in 30 years.

01:21.348 --> 01:26.420 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
His office corrected that today,
but Mr. Trump
tweeted that the congressman's
statement is

01:26.453 --> 01:29.189 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
-- quote -- "Wrong or lie.

01:29.222 --> 01:35.462 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
He boycotted Bush 43 also
because he thought
it would be hypocritical to
attend."

01:35.495 --> 01:37.931 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Trump followed up later on FOX
News.

01:37.965 --> 01:42.235 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
DONALD TRUMP (R),
President-Elect: I think
he just grandstanded, John
Lewis, and then

01:42.269 --> 01:43.870 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
he got caught in a very bad lie.

01:43.904 --> 01:45.439 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
So, let's see what happens.

01:45.472 --> 01:48.508 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
As far as other people not
going, that's OK,
because we need seats so badly.

01:48.542 --> 01:50.911 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
I hope they will give me their
tickets.

01:50.944 --> 01:56.016 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Mr. Trump flew to
Washington
tonight for a dinner honoring
Tom Barrack,

01:56.049 --> 01:59.753 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
a longtime friend who heads the
Inauguration
Committee.

01:59.786 --> 02:04.691 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Meanwhile, Russian President
Vladimir Putin
accused the Obama administration
of trying

02:04.725 --> 02:06.526 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
to sabotage the president-elect.

02:06.560 --> 02:12.933 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Putin dismissed reports that the
Kremlin has
compromising information on Mr.
Trump, including

02:12.966 --> 02:16.937 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
using prostitutes in Moscow
during a Miss
Universe pageant.

02:16.970 --> 02:20.273 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
VLADIMIR PUTIN, Russian
President (through
translator): I do not know Mr.
Trump.

02:20.307 --> 02:21.508 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
I have never met him.

02:21.541 --> 02:23.877 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I do not know what he will do on
the international
scene.

02:23.910 --> 02:28.515 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
So I have no grounds for
attacking him, criticizing
him for something or protecting
him in any

02:28.548 --> 02:30.350 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
way.

02:30.384 --> 02:33.053 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
We won't even appeal to the
Nobel Prize Committee
if he is awarded with a Nobel
Prize.

02:33.086 --> 02:37.557 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: The White House
rejected Putin's
criticism, and said -- quote --
"There is

02:37.591 --> 02:40.394 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
a pretty stark divide here."

02:40.427 --> 02:46.233 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
President Obama today commuted
the prison
sentence of Chelsea Manning for
passing classified

02:46.266 --> 02:49.870 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
military and diplomatic files to
WikiLeaks.

02:49.903 --> 02:55.609 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
The former U.S. Army
intelligence analyst
is serving a sentence of 35
years.

02:55.642 --> 03:00.714 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
She is one of 209 inmates who
received commutations
today.

03:00.747 --> 03:03.450 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Another 64 received pardons.

03:03.483 --> 03:07.154 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Charlie Savage is covering the
story for The
New York Times.

03:07.187 --> 03:10.457 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Charlie Savage, remind us what
Chelsea Manning
was originally charged with.

03:10.490 --> 03:12.192 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
CHARLIE SAVAGE, The New York
Times: Hi.

03:12.225 --> 03:14.027 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Yes, thanks for having me on.

03:14.061 --> 03:19.866 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So, when Chelsea Manning was
arrested in 2010
and charged with passing
documents to WikiLeaks,

03:19.900 --> 03:25.772 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
she was charged with numerous
accounts of
violating the Espionage Act and
also was charged

03:25.806 --> 03:31.211 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
with aiding the enemy, which is
essentially
the military justice system's
version of treason.

03:31.244 --> 03:36.817 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
She was convicted of the
Espionage Act charges,
most of them, but was acquitted
of aiding

03:36.850 --> 03:38.618 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
the enemy.

03:38.652 --> 03:43.757 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And she was sentenced to 35
years in prison,
which is dramatically longer
than any other

03:43.790 --> 03:48.295 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
prison sentence ever carried out
in the American
justice system for a leak case.

03:48.328 --> 03:52.666 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: And do we know
why the president
decided to commute her sentence?

03:52.699 --> 03:58.705 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
CHARLIE SAVAGE: So, there was a
briefing call
with senior White House
officials after the

03:58.738 --> 04:01.241 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
commutations and pardons were
announced.

04:01.274 --> 04:05.212 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And the senior White House
official -- we
were not allowed to name them
under the ground

04:05.245 --> 04:08.415 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
rules -- described a little bit
of the president's
thinking about this.

04:08.448 --> 04:15.522 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
He said, well, she admitted that
what she
had done was wrong and
apologized for it,

04:15.555 --> 04:23.463 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
and she expressed remorse and
has now been
serving nearly seven years in
prison for it.

04:23.497 --> 04:29.002 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And most people who have been
convicted in
leak cases -- there has been
about a dozen,

04:29.035 --> 04:33.840 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
most of them in the last eight
years -- have
been convicted -- have been
sentenced to one,

04:33.874 --> 04:36.476 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
two, or three years, not 35.

04:36.510 --> 04:42.916 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And so part of this was also the
equity of
making this sentence more in the
range of

04:42.949 --> 04:45.552 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
what other people accused of
similar conduct
have received.

04:45.585 --> 04:48.855 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: So, the question
is, what signal
does this send?

04:48.889 --> 04:53.193 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Tonight, the speaker of the
House, Paul Ryan,
has issued a statement saying --
quote -- "This

04:53.226 --> 04:54.961 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
is just outrageous."

04:54.995 --> 04:59.132 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
He says: "Chelsea Manning's
treachery put
American lives at risk and
exposed some of

04:59.166 --> 05:01.101 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
our nation's most sensitive
secrets."

05:01.134 --> 05:04.971 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And he says, "The president now
leaves in
place a dangerous precedent that
those who

05:05.005 --> 05:09.409 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
compromise our national security
won't be
held accountable for their
crimes."

05:09.442 --> 05:14.181 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
CHARLIE SAVAGE: That's one of
many statements
like that coming out of
Republicans on the

05:14.214 --> 05:15.982 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
Hill.

05:16.016 --> 05:19.519 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
We haven't heard yet from
president-elect
Trump on this, but that
statement is reflected

05:19.553 --> 05:23.223 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
by what other people like
Senator McCain and
others have said.

05:23.256 --> 05:28.562 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I would say, as a point of just
clarification,
none of the documents that
Chelsea Manning

05:28.595 --> 05:32.532 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
leaked were classified above the
nearly classified
level.

05:32.566 --> 05:34.734 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
That is to say, none of them
were top-secret.

05:34.768 --> 05:39.172 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
That was another thing that the
White House
discussed today in comparing her
to Edward

05:39.206 --> 05:43.009 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Snowden, who President Obama
declined to pardon.

05:43.043 --> 05:47.180 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So, to say they're some of the
most sensitive
secrets is an exaggeration.

05:47.214 --> 05:53.587 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And also military prosecutors at
her court-martial
didn't accuse her or present any
evidence

05:53.620 --> 05:57.090 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
that anyone was actually killed
as a result
of her leaks.

05:57.123 --> 06:04.664 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
On the other hand, the
government did scramble
afterward to move some people
out of potential

06:04.698 --> 06:09.936 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
harm's way who were named in
some of the documents
as having helped American
diplomats or troops

06:09.970 --> 06:14.007 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
in very dangerous countries,
lest they come
to harm.

06:14.040 --> 06:18.311 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So the fact that no one was
killed didn't
mean that it wasn't indeed
putting some people

06:18.345 --> 06:19.312 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
at risk.

06:19.346 --> 06:20.880 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And she has apologized for
having done that.

06:20.914 --> 06:24.384 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Charlie Savage
with The New
York Times, thank you very much.

06:24.417 --> 06:26.253 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
CHARLIE SAVAGE: Thank you.

06:26.286 --> 06:31.458 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Also tonight, new
numbers are
out on the consequences of
repealing Obamacare.

06:31.491 --> 06:36.329 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The Congressional Budget Office
assessed a
2016 bill that is the starting
point for this

06:36.363 --> 06:38.098 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
year's effort.

06:38.131 --> 06:43.370 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
It found some 18 million
Americans would lose
coverage within a year of
repeal, if there

06:43.403 --> 06:45.038 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
is no replacement.

06:45.071 --> 06:51.611 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The number would climb to 32
million by 2026,
again, assuming nothing replaces
it.

06:51.645 --> 06:55.215 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Republicans insisted today that
they will
have a replacement.

06:55.248 --> 07:00.820 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The nominee to be secretary of
the U.S. Interior
Department says it's -- quote --
"indisputable"

07:00.854 --> 07:05.458 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
that climate change is
happening, and that
humans are a big cause.

07:05.492 --> 07:10.430 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Montana Representative Ryan
Zinke spoke today
at his Senate confirmation
hearing.

07:10.463 --> 07:15.402 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Vermont Senator Bernie Sanders
pressed him
on president-elect Trump's
assertion that

07:15.435 --> 07:17.270 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
climate change is a hoax.

07:17.304 --> 07:18.405 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
REP.

07:18.438 --> 07:20.106 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
RYAN ZINKE (R), Montana: I don't
believe it's
a hoax.

07:20.140 --> 07:21.107 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
I believe we should...

07:21.141 --> 07:22.375 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
SEN.

07:22.409 --> 07:23.109 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
BERNIE SANDERS (I), Vermont: You
do not believe
it's a hoax?

07:23.143 --> 07:24.110 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
REP.

07:24.144 --> 07:25.111 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
RYAN ZINKE: No.

07:25.145 --> 07:26.112 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
I believe we should be prudent
to be prudent.

07:26.146 --> 07:27.113 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
That means, I don't know
definitively.

07:27.147 --> 07:28.982 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
SEN.

07:29.015 --> 07:32.552 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
BERNIE SANDERS: If climate
change is already
causing devastating problems,
should we allow

07:32.585 --> 07:36.389 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
fossil fuel to be drilled on
public lands?

07:36.423 --> 07:37.590 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
REP.

07:37.624 --> 07:40.093 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
RYAN ZINKE: Again, we need an
economy and
jobs, too.

07:40.126 --> 07:45.432 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Zinke also said
he is open
to drilling more on public
lands, and that

07:45.465 --> 07:49.202 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
he will review President Obama's
limits on
drilling in Alaska.

07:49.235 --> 07:55.642 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
In Turkey, authorities confirmed
they have
arrested an Uzbek national, and
said he confessed

07:55.675 --> 08:00.647 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
to killing 39 people at an
Istanbul club early
on New Year's Day.

08:00.680 --> 08:06.152 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The alleged gunman was captured
late Monday
at this apartment in Istanbul's
suburbs.

08:06.186 --> 08:11.791 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
The city's governor said
fingerprints there
matched prints from the crime
scene.

08:11.825 --> 08:18.465 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The search for a Malaysian
Airlines plane
has ended after three years,
$160 million

08:18.498 --> 08:20.266 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
and no answers.

08:20.300 --> 08:26.339 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Ships with high-tech gear
covered, in all,
nearly 50,000 square miles in
the Indian Ocean

08:26.373 --> 08:28.208 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
west of Australia.

08:28.241 --> 08:33.813 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Today, despite complaints from
family members,
Malaysia, Australia and China
shut down the

08:33.847 --> 08:39.152 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
official hunt for Flight 370 and
all 239 people
it carried.

08:39.185 --> 08:43.189 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
There has been a new migrant
disaster in the
Mediterranean.

08:43.223 --> 08:48.628 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The International Organization
for Migration
reports that almost 180 people
apparently

08:48.661 --> 08:52.732 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
drowned when a boat capsized off
Libya over
the weekend.

08:52.766 --> 08:57.137 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
That is based on interviews with
a handful
of survivors.

08:57.170 --> 09:02.175 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
British Prime Minister Theresa
May declared
today that her government wants
a clean break

09:02.208 --> 09:03.977 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
from the European Union.

09:04.010 --> 09:09.315 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
May laid out her thinking, as
Britain gets
ready to negotiate terms for
leaving the E.U.

09:09.349 --> 09:14.921 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
She confirmed it means an end to
Britain's
role in Europe's single market
and to travel

09:14.954 --> 09:18.057 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
without passports, but she also
issued a warning.

09:18.091 --> 09:21.394 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
THERESA MAY, British Prime
Minister: I know
there are some voices calling
for a punitive

09:21.428 --> 09:28.735 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
deal that punishes Britain and
discourages
other countries from taking the
same path.

09:28.768 --> 09:33.973 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
That would be an act of
calamitous self-harm
for the countries of Europe, and
it wouldn't

09:34.007 --> 09:36.709 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
be the act of a friend.

09:36.743 --> 09:40.713 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Britain wouldn't, indeed, we
could not accept
such an approach.

09:40.747 --> 09:46.152 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: May also promised
that Parliament
will be able to vote on the
final deal, likely

09:46.186 --> 09:48.288 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
in 2019.

09:48.321 --> 09:53.293 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Back in this country, big
automakers are announcing
plans for expansions, under
pressure from

09:53.326 --> 09:55.128 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
president-elect Trump.

09:55.161 --> 09:59.966 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Hyundai says that it will boost
its investment
in U.S. plants by 50 percent
over the next

09:59.999 --> 10:01.701 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
four years.

10:01.734 --> 10:07.740 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And General Motors will spend an
additional
