of the weakest
oversight in the country.

22:37.790 --> 22:42.428 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Supporters point to better gains
by African-American
and Latino students in those
schools.

22:42.461 --> 22:47.032 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Today, DeVos tried to assure
senators that
she is not an enemy of public
schools.

22:47.066 --> 22:51.136 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
BETSY DEVOS: The vast majority
of students
in this country will continue to
attend public

22:51.170 --> 22:52.671 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
schools.

22:52.705 --> 22:57.042 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
If confirmed, I will be a strong
advocate
for great public schools.

22:57.076 --> 23:01.113 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: As the hearing
continued
this evening, educators are also
watching

23:01.146 --> 23:08.287 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
