AIDS and hears voices and, at
times, spends
three weeks out of the month at
multiple hospitals

30:43.241 --> 30:45.077 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
around Houston.

30:45.110 --> 30:51.883 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Gurley is part of a promising
effort in the
U.S. health care system, honing
in on so-called

30:51.917 --> 30:57.756 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
super utilizers, patients with
complex problems
who frequent emergency rooms and
cost public

30:57.789 --> 30:59.891 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
and private insurers dearly.

30:59.925 --> 31:05.197 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Super utilizers make up just 5
percent of
the U.S. population, but they
account for

31:05.230 --> 31:07.299 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
50 percent of health care
spending.

31:07.332 --> 31:11.536 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
As health care costs continue to
rise, providers
are trying to find these
patients and get

31:11.570 --> 31:13.705 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
to the root of their problems.

31:13.739 --> 31:18.410 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
An effort to do just that
started in New Jersey's
poorest city, Camden.

31:18.443 --> 31:23.148 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Family physician Dr. Jeffrey
Brenner was inspired
by how police departments were
using crime

31:23.181 --> 31:25.484 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
data to detect hot spots.

31:25.517 --> 31:30.856 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
To find Camden's health care hot
spots, Brenner
dug into ambulance records and
E.R. data to

31:30.889 --> 31:34.092 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
show how high-cost patients were
shuttling
between city hospitals.

31:34.126 --> 31:35.894 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
DR.

31:35.927 --> 31:37.729 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
JEFFREY BRENNER, Camden
Coalition of Healthcare
Providers: In America, we're
medicalizing

31:37.763 --> 31:40.766 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
social problems, and we're
criminalizing social
problems, and we're wasting huge
amounts of

31:40.799 --> 31:42.601 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
public resources.

31:42.634 --> 31:48.006 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
SARAH VARNEY: To steer super
utilizers away
from expensive emergency care,
Brenner's team,

31:48.039 --> 31:52.878 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
including social workers Latonya
Oliver (ph)
and Bill Nice (ph), seek
patients out in local

31:52.911 --> 31:54.146 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
neighborhoods.

31:54.179 --> 31:55.580 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MAN: There's been a few patients
that I have
had like that.

31:55.614 --> 32:00.719 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
SARAH VARNEY: They work
intensively with people
like Peter Bowser (ph).

32:00.752 --> 32:06.591 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Bowser was once homeless, and
went to the
E.R. 28 times in one year.

32:06.625 --> 32:10.529 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MAN: Because I was telling
people when I was
staying in the shelter, I said,
when I get

32:10.562 --> 32:12.831 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
my place, I said, I'm going to
maintain it.

32:12.864 --> 32:16.868 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
SARAH VARNEY: But after they
helped get a
permanent roof over his head,
Bowser's trips

32:16.902 --> 32:18.603 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
to the E.R. all but stopped.

32:18.637 --> 32:22.874 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MAN: And I think you would
prefer to spend
your time here than the hospital
any day of

32:22.908 --> 32:24.442 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
the week.

32:24.476 --> 32:26.912 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
SARAH VARNEY: This high-touch,
data-driven
approach has yielded big
savings.

32:26.945 --> 32:31.850 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
E.R. visits for the first group
of patients
dropped by 40 percent, cutting
monthly hospital

32:31.883 --> 32:36.087 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
bills from $1.2 million to
$500,000.

32:36.121 --> 32:40.926 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The Affordable Care Act has
boosted efforts
like this around the country by
funding so-called

32:40.959 --> 32:45.831 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
accountable care organizations,
teams of health
care professionals who team up
to improve

32:45.864 --> 32:49.467 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
care, lower costs and reap the
savings.

32:49.501 --> 32:54.472 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And it was Brenner's pioneering
work in Camden
that inspired others, including
the program

32:54.506 --> 32:59.411 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
in Houston, a sprawling city
desperate to
aid its sickest and most
isolated patients.

32:59.444 --> 33:04.816 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
While the more than 100
hospitals here typically
know their own super utilizers,
they had no

33:04.850 --> 33:08.520 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
way of knowing the top users
across the entire
city.

33:08.553 --> 33:13.592 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Tackling that problem took
unprecedented planning
among typically disjointed city
and county

33:13.625 --> 33:15.760 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
agencies, hospitals and
nonprofits.

33:15.794 --> 33:21.066 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
WOMAN: And you know that guy
that you helped
me get appointments for the
other day?

33:21.099 --> 33:23.301 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
He apparently had warrants out
for his arrest.

33:23.335 --> 33:25.170 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
WOMAN: Oh, OK.

33:25.203 --> 33:28.874 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
SARAH VARNEY: Now, many of the
hospitals here,
including the county hospital,
Ben Taub, pool

33:28.907 --> 33:34.045 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
their data and send it to Kallol
Mahata, a
former oil industry I.T.
engineer with the

33:34.079 --> 33:37.582 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Patient Care Intervention
Center, who combines
it into one database.

33:37.616 --> 33:39.517 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
MAN: And we saw that breakdown
by EMS.

33:39.551 --> 33:44.389 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
SARAH VARNEY: Mahata and Dr.
David Buck, the
group's founder, help to
identify patients

33:44.422 --> 33:48.894 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
at the top of the list, the
outliers of the
outliers.

33:48.927 --> 33:53.465 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Some of the data comes from the
Houston Fire
Department's 911 calls.

33:53.498 --> 33:58.169 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
