parks and neighborhoods
to find the patients.

33:58.203 --> 34:02.240 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Firefighters and paramedics like
Thomas Pierrel
(ph) often know these residents
from those

34:02.274 --> 34:06.478 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
emergency calls, but, this time,
their mission
is different.

34:06.511 --> 34:07.979 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
MAN: We make appointments.

34:08.013 --> 34:09.147 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
We find specialists.

34:09.180 --> 34:12.050 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
We try to maximize the resources
that you
have.

34:12.083 --> 34:15.954 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
SARAH VARNEY: The results of
these intensive
interventions can be stunning.

34:15.987 --> 34:18.590 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Timmy Williams was dying when
Dayna Gurley
found him.

34:18.623 --> 34:22.193 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
DAYNA GURLEY: Has your blood
pressure been
that high in the past three or
four weeks?

34:22.227 --> 34:23.194 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
TIMMY WILLIAMS, Houston
Resident: Mm-hmm.

34:23.228 --> 34:24.195 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
DAYNA GURLEY: It has been?

34:24.229 --> 34:25.330 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
TIMMY WILLIAMS: Yes, the B.E. is
high.

34:25.363 --> 34:27.065 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
