patients stopped
showing up.

35:34.632 --> 35:36.434 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
DR.

35:36.468 --> 35:37.802 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
DAVID BUCK, Patient Care
Intervention Center:
Nobody wants to take ownership
of any of it.

35:37.836 --> 35:41.439 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The people just want ownership
of what they
have authority over.

35:41.473 --> 35:43.141 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
And that's really the issue.

35:43.174 --> 35:49.581 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
SARAH VARNEY: Back in Camden,
even Dr. Brenner
is less optimistic than he once
was.

35:49.614 --> 35:53.618 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
His office now overflows with
pillows and
kitchenware for clients they're
trying to

35:53.651 --> 35:57.989 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
place in housing, and he thinks
homelessness
and entrenched financial
interests in health

35:58.023 --> 35:59.424 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
care are the biggest barriers.

35:59.457 --> 36:01.092 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
DR.

36:01.126 --> 36:03.661 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JEFFREY BRENNER: I think this is
going to
take a lot longer than I ever
imagined.

36:03.695 --> 36:08.199 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I think we're in a 20-year arc
of recalibrating
and rethinking what is health
and what is

36:08.233 --> 36:12.771 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
